Subject: Re: [T2] Missing alternator cover

It covers the opening for the alternator adjustment nut on the type iv
engines. I believe it prevents the re circulation of hot gases back
into the engine compartment and cooling air streams. No analogous
equivalent for the type I engine. This is great news as this piece is
easily lost, and until now no "new" replacements have been available.


